history.content: Also 127 is pretty disorganized. As someone who took Math 110 a while ago, I found it very interesting and delves deep into the theory of linear algebra. But for purposes of studying Machine Learning etc. learning optimization theory from 127 is probably more useful. Although I do have to note there exists some overlap between the optimization in 127 and 189. Hope this helps!

So, I want to take a linear algebra course to prepare for CS189. As Sahai has often recommended on this piazza, EE127 is a better fit than Math 110. I've heard that EE127 is a really unorganized class, so I'm not sure whether to take it. The thing with Math 110 is that I might not get into it, given that there aren't any reserved seats for CoE students ( I think so, not sure). 

Which class should I enroll for?
history.subject: Math 110 vs EE127
